OL,3,CPlaque unveiled for Britain's first
OL,4,Cblack professional footballer
OL,6,FAfter leaving Ghana to train as a
OL,7,Fmissionary, Arthur came to the UK in
OL,8,F1882. As well as playing in goal for
OL,9,FNorth End, he was also ranked as the
OL,10,Fworld's fasted man - running 100
OL,11,Fmetres in just 10 seconds.
OL,13,FOriginally an amateur player for
OL,14,FDarlington, Arthur was spotted by
OL,15,FPreston North End when the two clubs
OL,16,Fplayed each other. After joining the
OL,17,Fclub, he helped them reach the FA Cup
OL,18,Fsemi-finals in 1887.
